205 to 193 Henry Street, north side, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Clinton Street, showwing the Anshei Bobruisk Synagogue (No. 203). The congregation was organized in 1892 and has an auxilary called the Ladies' Society. Services are conducted in Hebrew and Yiddish.
June 6, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
